1
00:00:12,570 --> 00:00:17,568
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language.)

2
00:00:27,546 --> 00:00:28,379
Wow, Ing.

3
00:00:28,379 --> 00:00:29,712
This place is so beautiful.

4
00:00:29,712 --> 00:00:31,171
Why did you just bring me here now?

5
00:00:32,004 --> 00:00:32,879
Well...

6
00:00:33,212 --> 00:00:35,421
This time it's more important
than the other times.

7
00:00:35,921 --> 00:00:37,129
How is it important?

8
00:00:37,129 --> 00:00:39,296
A belated birthday surprise for me, huh?

9
00:00:44,421 --> 00:00:45,504
Hello.

10
00:00:45,504 --> 00:00:47,087
Welcome.

11
00:00:47,087 --> 00:00:48,462
Reserved under the name Ing.

12
00:00:57,629 --> 00:00:58,962
Room 13.

13
00:00:59,296 --> 00:01:00,879
It's the most special room in our hotel.

14
00:01:00,879 --> 00:01:03,379
Perfect for guests who are ready
to open their hearts.

15
00:01:04,337 --> 00:01:05,212
Great.

16
00:01:05,212 --> 00:01:07,212
Tonight, we'll have a long chat.

17
00:01:09,671 --> 00:01:11,462
The room key is so cute.

18
00:01:11,462 --> 00:01:12,754
Let's go check out the room.

19
00:01:21,087 --> 00:01:22,337
Sometimes

20
00:01:22,379 --> 00:01:24,129
what we're afraid to say out loud

21
00:01:24,379 --> 00:01:27,587
might be the very thing
we're afraid not to say.

22
00:01:41,921 --> 00:01:44,254
Oh! The room is so cute.

23
00:01:44,837 --> 00:01:46,837
Just as cute as the two of us.

24
00:01:48,337 --> 00:01:50,296
Let me leave my bag with you.

25
00:02:04,379 --> 00:02:06,087
(Mom: Don't forget dinner
at Num's place this Sunday at 6 PM.)

26
00:02:06,087 --> 00:02:07,546
(Dad: Ing, just remember.
Their family chose us.)

27
00:02:07,546 --> 00:02:08,921
(Mom: Absolutely do not embarrass us.)

28
00:02:26,254 --> 00:02:27,337
What are you watching?

29
00:02:29,462 --> 00:02:31,754
Nothing. I'm just checking
some work emails.

30
00:02:32,129 --> 00:02:33,504
I'm starving now.

31
00:02:33,504 --> 00:02:34,296
Let's go change clothes.

32
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:51,546
Ing.

33
00:02:52,921 --> 00:02:54,171
Ing, are you okay?

34
00:02:55,171 --> 00:02:56,712
You hardly ate anything today.

35
00:02:57,504 --> 00:02:58,837
I'm not really hungry.

36
00:02:59,879 --> 00:03:01,087
That's not true.

37
00:03:02,046 --> 00:03:03,671
You were quiet in the car.

38
00:03:03,754 --> 00:03:05,671
You were quiet again
when we arrived at the hotel.

39
00:03:05,921 --> 00:03:07,587
And look at your face now.

40
00:03:07,712 --> 00:03:09,421
Your face says it all, Ing.

41
00:03:10,337 --> 00:03:11,712
What's wrong?

42
00:03:12,212 --> 00:03:13,712
You can tell me.

43
00:03:16,129 --> 00:03:16,879
Pat.

44
00:03:18,462 --> 00:03:19,296
If...

45
00:03:20,171 --> 00:03:22,171
I just disappeared one day,

46
00:03:22,337 --> 00:03:23,629
would you hate me?

47
00:03:24,004 --> 00:03:25,254
Disappear?

48
00:03:26,587 --> 00:03:27,629
Disappear where?

49
00:03:28,671 --> 00:03:30,087
This Sunday,

50
00:03:30,962 --> 00:03:32,754
my parents want to
set me up with someone.

51
00:03:33,546 --> 00:03:34,546
And...

52
00:03:38,796 --> 00:03:40,129
Do you want to marry him?

53
00:03:41,046 --> 00:03:42,046
No.

54
00:03:42,754 --> 00:03:45,171
I don't even know him.

55
00:03:45,962 --> 00:03:47,504
And I also

56
00:03:48,754 --> 00:03:50,712
already have someone I love.

57
00:03:51,962 --> 00:03:54,546
The person you love...

58
00:03:55,754 --> 00:03:57,046
Who is it, Ing?

59
00:04:05,587 --> 00:04:06,712
Shanghai.

60
00:04:07,546 --> 00:04:09,046
Just let me explain first, okay?

61
00:04:09,504 --> 00:04:11,379
Are you about to go abroad, Pat?

62
00:04:12,879 --> 00:04:13,754
Hmm.

63
00:04:15,546 --> 00:04:17,212
I've got a job there.

64
00:04:17,879 --> 00:04:20,129
I've planned that

65
00:04:20,296 --> 00:04:21,921
I'll leave in 2 months.

66
00:04:22,546 --> 00:04:23,712
That's funny, isn't it?

67
00:04:25,421 --> 00:04:27,087
I'm afraid of losing you,

68
00:04:27,379 --> 00:04:29,004
so I brought you here.

69
00:04:31,254 --> 00:04:32,254
And you

70
00:04:32,337 --> 00:04:34,212
are about to start a new life.

71
00:04:34,837 --> 00:04:36,129
No... It's...

72
00:04:36,421 --> 00:04:37,921
It's not what you think, Ing.

73
00:04:37,921 --> 00:04:39,504
Then what is it?

74
00:04:40,962 --> 00:04:43,962
I'm being forced
to get engaged to a stranger.

75
00:04:45,379 --> 00:04:46,212
But you

76
00:04:46,546 --> 00:04:48,962
are about to start
a new life in Shanghai

77
00:04:49,087 --> 00:04:50,837
without even telling me.

78
00:04:51,254 --> 00:04:52,212
I think

79
00:04:52,212 --> 00:04:54,837
that you will never see me
the way I see you.

80
00:04:54,837 --> 00:04:55,837
And...

81
00:04:57,046 --> 00:05:00,462
If I told you about Shanghai,

82
00:05:01,212 --> 00:05:03,546
I guess I might have overestimated
my importance to you.

83
00:05:05,296 --> 00:05:07,837
In the end, we're the same, you know.

84
00:05:08,962 --> 00:05:10,254
Both of us

85
00:05:12,296 --> 00:05:14,462
made decisions
without telling each other.

86
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:19,504
But the difference is

87
00:05:20,129 --> 00:05:21,462
I was forced.

88
00:05:23,629 --> 00:05:24,462
And you

89
00:05:24,712 --> 00:05:25,837
chose yourself.

90
00:05:27,212 --> 00:05:27,837
Ing.

91
00:05:27,962 --> 00:05:28,754
Wait.

92
00:05:29,712 --> 00:05:30,504
Ing.

93
00:06:00,462 --> 00:06:02,504
You can run away from others,

94
00:06:04,421 --> 00:06:07,296
but can you run away
from your own heart?

95
00:06:08,254 --> 00:06:09,629
Have you ever faced a choice

96
00:06:10,046 --> 00:06:12,587
where every path leads to pain?

97
00:06:14,754 --> 00:06:16,629
All I know is that

98
00:06:18,587 --> 00:06:20,962
the more we love,

99
00:06:22,087 --> 00:06:23,879
the more we fear hearing

100
00:06:25,337 --> 00:06:27,837
"It's too late."

101
00:06:33,254 --> 00:06:34,504
But if we

102
00:06:35,337 --> 00:06:36,879
must choose to be hurt,

103
00:06:40,962 --> 00:06:42,004
dear,

104
00:06:42,087 --> 00:06:43,504
then the pain that comes
from having the courage

105
00:06:43,671 --> 00:06:44,754
to speak the truth

106
00:06:46,129 --> 00:06:47,962
will always be lighter

107
00:06:48,921 --> 00:06:50,296
than the pain of staying silent.

108
00:07:10,754 --> 00:07:11,462
Ing,

109
00:07:12,796 --> 00:07:14,212
I'm sorry

110
00:07:14,629 --> 00:07:16,754
for not telling you about Shanghai.

111
00:07:17,879 --> 00:07:19,754
I'm sorry too,

112
00:07:21,629 --> 00:07:23,168
for not telling you
about the engagement.

113
00:07:24,921 --> 00:07:26,254
We're both

114
00:07:26,837 --> 00:07:28,171
so messed up, aren't we?

115
00:07:42,337 --> 00:07:42,837
Pat,

116
00:07:44,254 --> 00:07:45,379
I really need to ask you something.

117
00:07:46,629 --> 00:07:47,921
- If it weren't for Shanghai,
- If it weren't for your families,

118
00:07:48,004 --> 00:07:49,212
- would you have chosen me, Pat?
- would you have chosen me, Ing?

119
00:07:55,629 --> 00:07:57,212
I've felt more than

120
00:07:57,671 --> 00:07:59,462
just friendship for you for a long time.

121
00:08:00,837 --> 00:08:01,754
But

122
00:08:02,837 --> 00:08:04,879
every time I try to say it,

123
00:08:05,504 --> 00:08:08,046
my parents' voices are always louder.

124
00:08:11,421 --> 00:08:14,379
"Don't disappoint the family, Ing."

125
00:08:14,671 --> 00:08:18,712
I've been stuck on this idea
of being a dutiful daughter.

126
00:08:19,379 --> 00:08:21,046
That in the end,

127
00:08:21,046 --> 00:08:23,546
I forget to ask myself,

128
00:08:23,962 --> 00:08:25,212
"What about my heart?"

129
00:08:27,879 --> 00:08:29,671
I'm scared, too.

130
00:08:31,087 --> 00:08:32,046
I'm scared

131
00:08:32,921 --> 00:08:36,087
that my parents
will find out I like girls.

132
00:08:36,837 --> 00:08:39,754
They would be disappointed in me.

133
00:08:40,962 --> 00:08:42,796
And I'm scared

134
00:08:42,962 --> 00:08:44,962
that everything I have now

135
00:08:45,212 --> 00:08:47,379
will fall apart.

136
00:08:48,879 --> 00:08:51,046
So I chose to run away.

137
00:08:51,379 --> 00:08:55,087
I don't want you to see
how cowardly I am.

138
00:09:01,837 --> 00:09:03,129
Then,

139
00:09:04,462 --> 00:09:05,546
now,

140
00:09:06,296 --> 00:09:08,629
can we stop running away for once?

141
00:09:12,504 --> 00:09:13,504
I...

142
00:09:13,837 --> 00:09:15,587
love you, Pat.

143
00:09:19,421 --> 00:09:20,462
Love like...

144
00:09:20,462 --> 00:09:22,546
Not just as a friend.

145
00:09:24,796 --> 00:09:27,754
And I don't want to marry anyone
unless it's you, Pat.

146
00:09:34,129 --> 00:09:35,921
I love you too, Ing.

147
00:09:38,129 --> 00:09:39,504
So much.

148
00:09:40,171 --> 00:09:41,504
So much

149
00:09:41,629 --> 00:09:43,754
that if you get any closer,

150
00:09:44,254 --> 00:09:46,712
I won't have the strength to walk away.

151
00:09:55,348 --> 00:09:58,970
♪Before it's too late, I need to say♪

152
00:09:59,962 --> 00:10:03,678
♪I'm in love with you in every way♪

153
00:10:03,872 --> 00:10:06,528
♪Don't wanna
marry someone I don't choose♪

154
00:10:06,624 --> 00:10:11,487
♪Don't wanna wake up without you♪

155
00:10:13,837 --> 00:10:16,921
(Do we still have the right
to choose each other?)

156
00:10:18,462 --> 00:10:19,337
Yes, we do.

157
00:10:20,379 --> 00:10:23,587
As long as we don't let anyone
choose for us,

158
00:10:24,629 --> 00:10:26,880
we always have that right, Ing.

159
00:10:27,290 --> 00:10:31,128
♪Before it's too late, we found our way♪

160
00:10:31,264 --> 00:10:35,324
♪Two hearts that chose love anyway♪

161
00:10:36,044 --> 00:10:40,448
♪You're mine forever, I am yours♪

162
00:10:40,448 --> 00:10:45,056
♪This is what we're fighting for♪

163
00:10:45,312 --> 00:10:47,264
♪Not too late, we made it through♪

164
00:10:47,264 --> 00:10:49,696
♪Not too late, I'm here with you♪

165
00:10:49,696 --> 00:10:51,680
♪Before it's gone, we held on tight♪

166
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:54,136
♪We chose our love, and that's alright♪

167
00:10:54,752 --> 00:11:00,352
♪Not too late, not too late♪

168
00:11:00,352 --> 00:11:05,056
♪We chose love before too late♪

169
00:11:07,879 --> 00:11:09,504
No matter what happens,

170
00:11:10,129 --> 00:11:11,629
I will be right here,

171
00:11:12,212 --> 00:11:13,587
not running away anymore.

172
00:11:19,546 --> 00:11:21,004
Ing, where did you go last night?

173
00:11:21,087 --> 00:11:22,754
Why didn't you answer my call?

174
00:11:22,796 --> 00:11:23,796
Don't you remember?

175
00:11:23,796 --> 00:11:26,879
You have to meet his family
on Sunday, right?

176
00:11:27,546 --> 00:11:28,504
Mom,

177
00:11:28,796 --> 00:11:30,004
about that,

178
00:11:30,587 --> 00:11:32,629
I want to clear things up today.

179
00:11:33,754 --> 00:11:36,629
What do you mean by saying that?

180
00:11:38,046 --> 00:11:39,712
I'm not getting engaged, Mom.

181
00:11:41,337 --> 00:11:43,171
Before we finally got this opportunity,

182
00:11:43,212 --> 00:11:45,421
did you ever think
about our family's future?

183
00:11:45,712 --> 00:11:47,046
I've thought about it.

184
00:11:47,754 --> 00:11:49,712
I think about you every day,

185
00:11:50,587 --> 00:11:52,587
to the point where I forget
to think about myself.

186
00:11:53,046 --> 00:11:55,671
And forget about
the person I truly love.

187
00:11:57,212 --> 00:11:58,212
Mom,

188
00:11:59,212 --> 00:12:01,212
I love a woman,

189
00:12:02,254 --> 00:12:05,379
and she's standing right next to me.

190
00:12:07,379 --> 00:12:09,212
If my future

191
00:12:09,296 --> 00:12:10,587
has to be exchanged

192
00:12:10,587 --> 00:12:12,421
for lying to my own heart,

193
00:12:12,504 --> 00:12:13,629
I don't want it.

194
00:12:14,254 --> 00:12:17,754
Just don't come crying to me later.

195
00:12:24,837 --> 00:12:26,296
Thank you so much

196
00:12:27,129 --> 00:12:28,587
for choosing me,

197
00:12:28,796 --> 00:12:32,129
even though it's so difficult.

198
00:12:33,421 --> 00:12:35,254
Thank you for "being here"

199
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:38,796
even while you're heading to Shanghai.

200
00:12:39,671 --> 00:12:41,254
About Shanghai,

201
00:12:41,504 --> 00:12:44,004
there's something I haven't told you.

202
00:12:45,129 --> 00:12:46,296
What else is there?

203
00:12:46,629 --> 00:12:47,921
Don't tell me

204
00:12:47,921 --> 00:12:50,462
you've got a new job on the moon too.

205
00:12:50,962 --> 00:12:52,504
No.

206
00:12:52,504 --> 00:12:53,504
That's funny.

207
00:12:54,837 --> 00:12:55,671
Well,

208
00:12:56,629 --> 00:12:59,046
I don't want to go
to Shanghai alone anymore.

209
00:13:01,046 --> 00:13:02,212
Ing,

210
00:13:02,629 --> 00:13:05,837
do you want to start
a new life together?

211
00:13:06,212 --> 00:13:09,587
Going there as my partner.

212
00:13:10,337 --> 00:13:11,962
Can I really go?

213
00:13:13,254 --> 00:13:15,046
As a couple.

214
00:13:15,671 --> 00:13:17,629
Not a child running away from home.

215
00:13:18,629 --> 00:13:20,421
Sure, darling.

216
00:13:21,129 --> 00:13:23,046
We don't have to run
from anyone anymore.

217
00:13:23,212 --> 00:13:24,296
We'll just

218
00:13:25,171 --> 00:13:27,212
keep walking hand in hand like this.

219
00:13:28,004 --> 00:13:29,046
Well then...

220
00:13:29,379 --> 00:13:31,296
Give me a moment to save up money.

221
00:13:32,254 --> 00:13:33,504
Sell a kidney...

222
00:13:33,546 --> 00:13:34,712
Sell the heart...

223
00:13:35,421 --> 00:13:36,254
No.

224
00:13:36,421 --> 00:13:38,587
I'll keep my heart for you alone.

225
00:13:39,921 --> 00:13:40,837
Oh...

226
00:13:41,671 --> 00:13:44,004
You still have the mood
to joke like this.

227
00:13:44,546 --> 00:13:45,921
Look at the tears.

228
00:13:45,921 --> 00:13:47,462
You've cried them all out.

229
00:13:49,337 --> 00:13:50,546
You did a great job.

230
00:14:06,296 --> 00:14:07,254
This ring

231
00:14:07,504 --> 00:14:09,421
symbolizes our promise.

232
00:14:13,004 --> 00:14:14,671
The same for me, darling.

233
00:14:28,379 --> 00:14:30,837
Want to take a seat? Sit down.

234
00:14:49,296 --> 00:14:53,046
Another couple. Brave enough
to love in their own way.

235
00:14:54,921 --> 00:14:58,421
What about you, my beautiful dear?

236
00:14:58,421 --> 00:14:59,962
How are things going?

237
00:15:01,087 --> 00:15:06,212
I think it's almost my turn now.

238
00:15:21,178 --> 00:15:27,552
♪Only questions remain
why, what, and when♪

239
00:15:27,712 --> 00:15:31,389
♪That changed you so♪

240
00:15:31,969 --> 00:15:35,725
♪How do I understand♪

241
00:15:37,152 --> 00:15:43,754
♪Or is my heart given to you not enough♪

242
00:15:43,933 --> 00:15:47,884
♪My efforts still not enough♪

243
00:15:48,055 --> 00:15:52,420
♪Or do you not want me♪

244
00:15:53,048 --> 00:15:57,440
♪You've never seriously
thought about it♪
